body.description: Pack to the max with luggage that is truly all your own. The max carry-on expandable Rollaboard is designed for total packing versatility and customizable with a variety of interchangeable Travelpro exclusive zip-in organizers. Included inside the lid is a removable zip-in garment organizer, ideal for storing folded shirts, dresses and jackets. Also available for purchase separately are four additional coordinating Travelpro exclusive zip-in organizers-a laundry organizer for bathing suits, workout clothes and other damp items, A packing cubes organizer for shorts, shirts and accessories, A suitor organizer to keep hanging clothes wrinkle-free and an all-in-one organizer for wet and dry storage (each sold separately). created for domestic travel on larger aircraft, this bag is sized to max out the sizer bin and fit In the overhead bins of most major yours. Airlines. It also features a tip-resistant zippered expansion to increase packing space up to two inches, but be careful not to overpack the exterior pockets and risk making it too big for the sizer bin. Enjoy total convenience with a built-in USB port and dedicated exterior power bank pocket, exterior padded laptop pocket and removable TSA-compliant toiletries bag that stores perfectly in a same-sized exterior pocket. Two ultra-strong, oversized, high-performance ball bearing wheels roll smoothly over any terrain led by a four-stop, height-adjustable PowerScope handle, while the add-a-bag strap and metal j-hook let you carry additional bags hands-free. Built for professional-grade dependability With robust corner armor, skid guards and heavy-duty wheel housings, crew versapack is the civilian version of the luggage flight crews use, tested to meet the same superior quality and durability standards. This Rollaboard is further backed by the comprehensive built for a lifetime limited warranty with our trusted companion promise.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 27, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars a great carry on bag
reviews.reviewText: This is a great carry on bag. Plenty of pockets, the inside can be swapped out for various configs (sold separately; I have just used the default so far). This version is slightly less maneuverable as it only has two static wheels vs 4 on swivels. The 2 wheel version keeps a little more room inside compared to the 4 wheel version, and the larger wheels travel over uneven surfaces better. Also I got the "international" version which is slightly smaller than the domestic version to insure fit in non-US airlines.All in all, good design with external usb port for charging and separate pocket for the a power bank (not USB C though), main compartment has lockable zippers. Extendable handle works well and feels solid. External pocket with clear TSA pouch for toiletries.

reviews.reviewText: Great Carry-On. Probably the largest possible bag that passes for a Carry-On. Wheels roll super smooth and has all the interior pockets you need to organize your trip. I wanted big. This is the biggest I've found. I can pack a suit (44R), 2 dress shirts, 2 golf shirts, 1 pair of jeans, 2 pair golf shorts, 2 pair workout short, 2 workout shirts, 3 t-shirts, a bathing suit, underwear, socks, dress shoes, tennis shoes, and flips. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 1, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good size and sturdy
reviews.reviewText: I got this carry on because the main airport I frequent has carpet (which I hate) and that makes it difficult to push a four wheeled bag along (so, I’m getting old 😂). The wheels on this bag are smooth and glide over the carpet - yay! I chose the 19” so that if I’m on one of those smaller commuter jets it will still fit in the overhead. It still has lots more room than my underseat carry on. I don’t like having to check my bag at the gate because I then have to carry my 2nd bag to my connecting flight or baggage pick up. I really like the built-in charger for my phone while I’m waiting at the airport. This is the bag that the flight crew uses, for a reason, and it might be a tad heavier than the regular one, but not much. It is built to last, and has so many great features; I think it’s worth it.
